  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Monday. Social studies class with Mr. Pan is, without a doubt, the class most likely to put an entire room of students to sleep.",
      "zh": "星期一。上潘老師的社會課，絕對是最容易讓整間教室的學生睡著的一堂課，沒有之一。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Today's topic was how ancient kingdoms slowly turned into modern nations, which Mr. Pan somehow finds fascinating.",
      "zh": "今天的主題是古代王國如何慢慢演變成現代國家，不知為何潘老師覺得這個話題超級有趣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A nation is not just land,\" he said, drawing a rough map on the board. \"It is people who agree to be governed together, under one government.\"",
      "zh": "「一個國家不只是土地，」他一邊在黑板上畫著簡陋的地圖一邊說：「而是一群同意接受同一個政府共同治理的人民。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, sitting next to me, whispered that this sounded suspiciously like our group project rules, and honestly, she had a point.",
      "zh": "坐我旁邊的 Bernice 小聲說，這聽起來很像我們分組報告的規矩，老實說，她講得還真有道理。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan explained how many nations fought long, difficult wars for independence, wanting freedom from an older, more powerful government.",
      "zh": "潘老師解釋了許多國家如何打了漫長又艱難的戰爭爭取獨立，想要脫離一個更古老、更強大的政府，獲得自由。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Freedom sounds simple,\" he said, \"but building a fair government after independence is often the hardest part.\"",
      "zh": "「自由聽起來很簡單，」他說：「但獨立之後要建立一個公平的政府，往往才是最困難的部分。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "He talked about a president who once led his young nation through a serious crisis, a moment when the whole government almost fell apart.",
      "zh": "他講到一位總統，曾經帶領他年輕的國家撐過一場嚴重的危機，那時整個政府差點就垮台了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A crisis tests everything,\" Mr. Pan said. \"It tests laws, it tests leaders, and honestly, it tests how much people trust each other.\"",
      "zh": "「一場危機會考驗所有的東西，」潘老師說：「考驗法律、考驗領導者，老實說，也考驗人民彼此之間的信任程度。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "I raised my hand and asked what happens when two nations cannot agree and a small conflict grows into a bigger one.",
      "zh": "我舉手問，如果兩個國家談不攏，一個小衝突演變成更大的衝突，那會怎麼樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That,\" Mr. Pan said, \"is exactly why we have laws, courts, and judges, both inside a nation and between different nations.\"",
      "zh": "「這，」潘老師說：「正是為什麼我們需要法律、法庭跟法官，不管是在一個國家內部，還是不同國家之間。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "To make the lesson less boring, he split us into groups for a pretend court case, and somehow I ended up as the judge.",
      "zh": "為了讓這堂課不要那麼無聊，他把我們分組來演一場模擬法庭，不知怎麼地，我最後變成了法官。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice played a prisoner accused of a ridiculous crime: stealing the last dumpling from the school cafeteria.",
      "zh": "Bernice 演一位被指控犯下一件荒謬罪行的犯人：偷走學校餐廳最後一顆水餃。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Order in the court!\" I shouted, banging a ruler like a judge's hammer, which made half the class laugh out loud.",
      "zh": "「法庭肅靜！」我大喊，用一把尺子敲桌子當作法官的槌子，全班有一半的人都笑出聲來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The \"trial\" lasted about five minutes and ended with Bernice's character found guilty of being extremely hungry, not actually guilty of any real crime.",
      "zh": "這場「審判」大概只進行了五分鐘，最後判定 Bernice 的角色只是「非常餓」有罪，並沒有真的犯下任何罪行。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Even William's class, Mr. Pan mentioned, is learning about voting and how citizens choose their own government through an election.",
      "zh": "潘老師提到，就連 William 那個年級，也正在學投票，以及公民如何透過選舉選出自己的政府。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Voting feels small,\" he said, \"but it is one way ordinary people help decide the direction of their whole nation.\"",
      "zh": "「投票感覺很微小，」他說：「但這是一般人幫忙決定整個國家方向的一種方式。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the end of class, my brain felt full of governments, presidents, crises, and one very dramatic dumpling trial.",
      "zh": "下課的時候，我腦子裡塞滿了政府、總統、危機，還有一場超級誇張的水餃審判。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan ended with an announcement: next month, the whole class will hold a formal debate about a real school policy.",
      "zh": "潘老師最後宣布了一件事：下個月，全班要就一項真正的校規舉行一場正式的辯論。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Pick your side carefully,\" he warned. \"A good debate is not about who shouts loudest, it is about who argues with the clearest reason.\"",
      "zh": "「小心選你要站的那一邊，」他提醒我們：「一場好的辯論，靠的不是誰喊得最大聲，而是誰講的道理最清楚。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice immediately announced she wants to be on my team, mostly because she enjoyed banging the ruler more than I expected.",
      "zh": "Bernice 馬上宣布她想跟我同一組，主要是因為她敲尺子敲得比我預期的還開心。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: social studies class may be sleepy, but apparently I have hidden talent as a very strict, ruler-banging judge.",
      "zh": "今日心得：社會課或許讓人昏昏欲睡，但我似乎有隱藏的天分，可以當一位很嚴格、很愛敲尺子的法官。"
    }
  ],
